edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp

Class TransformationCache

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.TransformationCache

  • public class TransformationCache
extends java.lang.Object
    Class containing several static fields and getters and setters for lists of elements that are often required in the transformation, but require a complete traversal of the model. The functions in this class are meant to pre-compute and cache these lists (e.g., relevant concrete resources, relevant working principles, and all object flows).
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Sebastian

        public static void rebuildCache(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element rootElement,
                org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Activity functionalSpecification)
        Rebuild all cached mappings and collections / sets.

        This function will rebuild the various lists. Rebuilding is performed by parsing the model, typically starting from the root model element.

        Parameters:
        rootElement - The root model element.
        functionalSpecification - The functional specification (used in determining relevant items)

      • rebuildListOfResources

        public static java.util.ArrayList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element> rebuildListOfResources(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element rootElement,
                                                                       org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Activity functionalSpecification)
        Rebuilds the list of concrete resources (including composites) that are relevant within the context of a particular functional specification.

        Simply calls DSEMLUtils.getConcreteResources(Element, Activity).

        Parameters:
        rootElement - The root model element.
        functionalSpecification - The functional specification.
        Returns:

      • rebuildListOfAllResources

        public static java.util.ArrayList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element> rebuildListOfAllResources(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element rootElement,
                                                                          org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Activity functionalSpecification)
        Rebuilds a list of ALL resources (including abstract types) that are relevant within the context of a particular functional specification.

        Simply calls DSEMLUtils.getAllResources(Element, Activity).

        Parameters:
        rootElement - The root model element.
        functionalSpecification - The functional specification.
        Returns:
        An ordered list of abstract and non-abstract resources relevant to the functional specification.

      • rebuildListOfCompositeResources

        public static java.util.ArrayList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element> rebuildListOfCompositeResources(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element rootElement)
        Rebuild list of composite resources.

        A precondition for this function is that the list of concrete resources has already been rebuilt.

        Simply calls DSEMLUtils.getCompositeResources(ArrayList) with the list of concrete, relevant resources as argument.

        Parameters:
        rootElement - The root model element.
        Returns:
        A list of relevant, concrete aggregate resources.
